snippet.textDisplay: As a beauty therapist and learning what ingredients are toxic to your skin pls pls pls don’t use products this cheap! Do your research on what products are good and bad for your skin, it may leave your skin soft and clear it, but over time it can cause damage, same with the hair products, she said the shampoo dried her hair out which means it has stripped all the natural oils out, which we need for our hair to grow. Conditioners that leave your hair feeling soft, usually contain a lot of sulfate, silicone, which also causes damage to your hair. Products are on the pricier side because manufacturers spend a lot of money making them so they are worth buying for your skin, not only that they spend so much time researching and testing it out. Buying cheap products now is only gonna cost you a lot more in the future when you’re going to dermatologists to fix your skin x
snippet.textOriginal: As a beauty therapist and learning what ingredients are toxic to your skin pls pls pls don’t use products this cheap! Do your research on what products are good and bad for your skin, it may leave your skin soft and clear it, but over time it can cause damage, same with the hair products, she said the shampoo dried her hair out which means it has stripped all the natural oils out, which we need for our hair to grow. Conditioners that leave your hair feeling soft, usually contain a lot of sulfate, silicone, which also causes damage to your hair. Products are on the pricier side because manufacturers spend a lot of money making them so they are worth buying for your skin, not only that they spend so much time researching and testing it out. Buying cheap products now is only gonna cost you a lot more in the future when you’re going to dermatologists to fix your skin x

snippet.textDisplay:
I love your videos! Just a tip for your Alex drawers, I had the same issue!!
basically my dad just went to a store close to us that sells screws etc and diy bits like that and explained what was happening. then we just took all the ikea screws out and then re screwed them in with the new screws. The problem is the ikea screws aren't brilliant when you're constantly opening the drawers and they have heavy things in. so the metal bit like unattaches from the screw if that makes sense! some stronger screws will work - just put them in the holes on the metal strips, hope it helps let me know if you need anything else!xxx
